body_html:
Further analysis on this test shows that there is a check for endianness. In case of BIG endian, test fails with "Unimplemented: Reading a bundle with different endianness from the reader".
I tried to bypass this check and allowed the execution further for this test however it gives wrong output.
The tensor bundle write/read seems to be working for big endian so now suspecting that the test data for big endian systems can be uploaded separately. But not sure how to generate the test data.
Can you please confirm this understanding is correct? Also, could you let us know the steps which will generate test data.
@aselle @poxvoculi Could you please provide your inputs on this?

I tried to bypass this check and allowed the execution further for this test however it gives wrong output. 
The tensor bundle write/read seems to be working for big endian so now suspecting that the test data for big endian systems can be uploaded separately. But not sure how to generate the test data.
